Durban - A man who began raping his stepdaughter from the time she was four years old until she was a teenager received five terms of life imprisonment in the Richard Bay Magistrate's Court. The man was also found guilty of sexually assaulting the victim's 11-year-old friend during a visit in 2016. "The accused raped his stepdaughter when she was four years old as from 2005 until 2016 and also sexually assaulted her friend, 11,  at Richards Bay during a visit," said Captain Nqobile Gwala. Gwala said cases of rape and sexual assault were opened at Richards Bay police station and the docket was transferred to Empangeni Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit who immediately arrested the accused. "He was taken to court and was released on bail until his conviction," said Gwala. National Child Protection Week will begin on Sunday until June 9. It is observed in South Africa annually to raise awareness of the rights of children. POST